Anonymous Tue 31 Aug 2021 03:23:29 No.41290307 Report
Quoted By:
>>41289943
>but a lot of world building
I'll give a few opinions that may or may not be relevant since I haven't had time to read the whole thing. Besides being on Google Docs, the switching colors make it harder to read.

Onward!
When I worldbuild in my stories, it's not fluff.
Too many writers are willing to pad their settings with the kind of material I relegate to a backstory file. You know, like how the trains run on schedule, or why there's three different languages that evolved from separate dialects/jobs.
It's either relevant to the plot or sensory detail.
The problem with "deep lore" is most writers are going to screw up the details. It's like writing about guns: someone always knows more than you.
Be more like Hemingway. Say as little as possible. The people more knowledgeable on a point will fill in the details you left out, and the less informed will ask questions in here.
